The <strong><code>padding</code></strong> <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</a> property sets the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Box_Model/Introduction_to_the_CSS_box_model#padding-area">padding area</a> on all four sides of an element. It is a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Shorthand_properties">shorthand</a> for <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-top" title="The padding-top CSS property sets the height of the padding area on the top of an element."><code>padding-top</code></a>, <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-right" title="The padding-right CSS property sets the width of the padding area on the right of an element."><code>padding-right</code></a>, <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-bottom" title="The padding-bottom CSS property sets the height of the padding area on the bottom of an element."><code>padding-bottom</code></a>, and <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-left" title="The padding-left CSS property sets the width of the padding area to the left of an element."><code>padding-left</code></a>.